## Notes
Please read these notes carefully.

The Silver Advertising server uses a strike system. Strikes will expire after 90 days of being issued. The more strikes you have, the more ‚Äúcooked‚Äù you are. 5 strikes gives you a Server-kick and 7 gives you a Server-ban.

Server staff have rights to give you strikes if they feel like you did something bad. You can appeal a strike by DM‚Äôing SupportMail.

-----------------------------------

Severity: Low [1 Strike]

Spamming
Sending the same or similar messages repeatedly within a short period of time.

Chaining
Copying and sending the same message another member posted.

Ghost-Ping
Pinging a member and deleting the message immediately afterward.

Light Toxicity
Engaging in back-and-forth toxic arguments, causing unnecessary conflict, or being disruptive to the community.

Channel Misuse
Using a channel for something it's not intended for.

Flooding
Sending overly large messages or a high number of messages in a short span, disrupting the flow of conversation.

Light Impersonation
Impersonating someone else to make them violate or seem to be violating the Server Rules.


-----------------------------------


Severity: Moderate [2-3 Strikes]

NSFW/NSFL References/Content
Mentioning or referencing any form of NSFW content or behavior.

Immature Behaviour
Deliberately trolling, being disruptive, or seeking attention.

Member Disrespect
Speaking rudely, mocking, insulting, or being intentionally hostile toward other members.

Light Sexism
Making gender-based jokes, stereotypes, or comments that diminish or target a gender even if it was in a joking matter.

Encourage Rule Breaking
Making other members violate the rules or take actions that could lead to consequences.

Ignoring Staff/Chain of Command
Arguing with or ignoring staff after being issued a verbal warning to stop a specific behavior. Always follow the Chain of Command.


-----------------------------------


Severity: High [4+ Strikes]

Encouraging Suicidal Acts
Comments or statements like "kill yourself," "die," "you should die," "I wish you were dead," etc.

NSFW Content
Sharing NSFW images, videos, gifs, emotes, stickers, links, or websites containing extreme violence, gore, pornography, self-harm, or excessively sexual content (including baits).

Raiding
Organized by a groups of people joining the server to cause trouble or break rules intentionally.

Slurs and Bypassing Slurs
Use of derogatory terms, including but not limited to the N-word, or similar language, and Any form of bypassing them.

Death Threats
Threatening someone‚Äôs life with explicit statements or intentions.

Black Marketing
Buying or selling in-game items, accounts, or services for real-life currencies or products.

Exploiting
Using exploits, affiliating with exploit servers, discussing exploits, or sharing exploit tools.

Alting
Using Alts to bypass bans or other moderation actions.

Beaming
Attempting to compromise or successfully compromising other members' accounts using scam links, QR codes, or similar methods.

Animal Cruelty
Posting or discussing animal abuse content.


Major Sexism
Overtly sexist comments or behaviors that promote hate or discrimination based on gender.

Homophobia / Transphobia
Any slurs, jokes, hate speech, or disrespect directed toward LGBTQ+ individuals. This includes mocking gender identity, sexual orientation, pronouns, or transitioning.

IP Loggers
Sharing links or tools intended to log someone‚Äôs IP.

Major Impersonation
Impersonating someone else to make them violate Severe Rules. This includes using Bot commands to fake messages, sending messages then editing it before you report, etc.


